Java Brick Breaker Game

Description
This Java application implements a classic brick breaker game. The player controls a paddle to bounce a ball, aiming to break all bricks on the screen. The game includes features such as power-ups and sound effects.

Features
Paddle Control: Use the left and right arrow keys to move the paddle.
Ball and Brick Interaction: The ball bounces off the paddle and breaks bricks upon collision.
Score Tracking: Score increases as bricks are broken.
Game Over and Victory: Displays game over screen when the ball falls below the paddle or victory screen when all bricks are destroyed.
Power-Ups: Occasionally, power-ups drop from broken bricks, affecting gameplay.
Pause Functionality: Press 'P' to pause and resume the game.
Sound Effects: Includes sound effects for ball collisions and game events.

How to Play
Run the Main class.
Use the left and right arrow keys to move the paddle.
Bounce the ball to break bricks and earn points.
Avoid letting the ball fall below the paddle.
Break all bricks to win the game.

Technologies Used
Java
Swing (for GUI)
javax.sound.sampled (for sound effects)
Contributions
Contributions to enhance the game's features or fix issues are welcome. Please fork the repository and create a pull request.
